Author: jl777c#5810
Content: When another tool is added to the toolbox, it does not mean that all future work will use that new tool. just that the new tool is available to be used. In other words, if you add a hammer to a toolbox, it does not mean you start using the hammer instead of a screwdriver. it just means if you need to hammer something, you have a hammer

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: verushash is added to the available ac parameters. it does not mean that all future hashing will use verushash, just that verushash is available to be used

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: not sure why many people use mutually exclusive logic when they hear something, ie. something new exists -> everything old is replaced

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: that wouldnt be very backward compatible.
